INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('William Bain is here, dressed in his curiously outdated clothing, and he teaches you a spell. Gain 1 Spell.',NULL,'Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('William Bain isn''t here right now but a Nightgaunt is! You must immediately move to the open gate of your choice and enter it.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('William Bain offers to lend you a hand. You may immediately move to the open gate of your choice and enter it.',NULL,'Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('William Bain tells you that Nodens has sent one of his Nightgaunts to help you, but the journey will be dangerous. If you wish to accept the help, make a Will (-2) check. If you pass, move to the second area of any Other World you choose. If you fail, the Nightgaunt has left you lost in time and space.','Will -2','Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You are stunned to discover a mysterious man in exotic looking robes. He claims to have been waiting for you. If you are Cursed or have any Mask items, he tells you that he is called The Messenger and is meant to aid you. Take his Ally card or, if it is not available, gain 2 Clue tokens.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You can''t begin to fathom how old William Bain really is. He tells you the history of Kingsport as if he had witnessed the whole thing firsthand. Gain 2 Clue tokens.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You find William Bain''s company helps to calm your thoughts and heal your mind. You may either discard 1 Madness card if you have one or restore your Sanity to its maximum.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You just have one last chasm to cross, but it looks rather dangerous. Pass a Fight (-1) check or move to the Wireless Station.','Fight -1','Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You plead with William Bain for assistance. If you pass a Will (-1) check, he agrees and works a powerful spell. Remove all rift progress tokens from 1 rift, closing it immediately. If you fail, he refuses explaining that he cannot interfere with the world of man without endangering himself.','Will -1','Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You sit and chat with the pleasant, if old-fashioned, William Bain. He seems to be very poorly informed of the outside world, but extremely knowledgable of more exotic subjects. Nothing happens.',NULL,'Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You talk with William Bain for a time, and he grows increasingly nervous. If you are Cursed, you find yourself suddenly overwhelmed with terror and hurl yourself out the only door to the small house. As the door opens directly over the cliff, you fall to the sea below and are devoured. If you are not Cursed, you control yourself, and nothing happens.',NULL,'Kingsport Horror');
INSERT INTO strange_high_house_encounters VALUES ('You visit with the strange, otherworldly William Bain for awhile, when suddenly he hushes you, frantically locks the door and all the windows, and then douses the light. The two of you crouch in silence as a chilling shadow makes its way around the house, trying every door and window before leaving. You are delayed and lose 1 Sanity.',NULL,'Kingsport Horror');
